a woman whose social security files got 
lost in a bureaucratic shuffle finally got a check for 19000 in 
back benefits for the past 17 years 
irene oneil 86 of mandan said after getting the check 
thursday she wasnt sure exactly how she would spend the money 
i havent any idea she said but i have eight 
grandchildren and two sons and im sure i can find some place for 
it 
mrs oneil was getting monthly social security check based on 
the earnings of her late husband when she remarried in 1972 
under a law passed two years later her benefits should have 
been raised to reflect the higher earnings of her second husband 
said bruce haugen an aide to rep byron dorgan dnd 
