maturity slipped to 747 percent from 748 percent late thursday 
yields on threemonth treasury bills edged up to 815 percent as 
the discount added 1 basis point to 789 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills rose to 829 percent as the discount advanced 3 
basis points to 786 percent yields on oneyear bills rose to 845 
percent as the discount gained 2 basis points to 785 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest that banks charge on 
overnight loans to one another fell to 8 percent after peaking at 
9 percent during the day the rate was 9 percent late thursday 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

